I’m thrilled to share this easy and fun sensory art activity that I’ve partnered with Johnson & Johnson to come up with! We love bath time painting, especially Abby as she can paint to her heart’s content. Simple to do with your little ones for more bonding time, it’s also so easy to clean up! Simply shower Abby and the walls at the same time. 

This amazing bath time paint can be created with four items you can easily find at home. We love using our Johnson’s®️ Milk + Rice Bath, because this gentle soap packed with milk proteins, rice extracts, multiple vitamins and minerals that keeps Abby’s skin all nourished even when she’s painting away with her hands. 

Johnson’s Baby is also running a giveaway on their Facebook page, so do head over for a chance to win an exclusive Johnson’s Baby activity pack (worth $100).

node.text:
Today feels like a good day for an overdue intro post, so here goes! Hi to all my followers, new and old, I am Fynn, aka the mum from 🇸🇬 who loves creating fun learning activities with trash. 😆 That is still a fact after 6 years, but I found a bigger love to design learning activities that are fun for children and easy for busy parents. Here are 5 more fun facts about me:
🔴 I worked as a professional makeup artist for 3 years, and I did makeup for weddings, theatre shows and fashion shows for brands like Marc Jacobs, Hermès, D&G. 
🟠 I taught Chemistry in an IB college in Sweden for a year. And in the afternoon after school, I worked part time at a bridal studio or walked around the town taking photos. Ahh, all the fun things I did before kids came along. 😊
🟡 The longest I stayed at a place was 2.5years. Since I married my husband in 2009, we moved 8 times in 12 years. I think we are finally settled down and hopefully we will break the 2.5years record at our current place. 
🟢 I LOVE fantasy stories/ movies with another world, superheros, magic or mythical creatures  like Harry Potter, Avengers, Fantastic Beasts, How to Train Your Dragon. I secretly wish I have a Night Fury as my pet. 
🔵 I really dread folding and ironing clothes and I can’t decide which one I dread more. Send me a folding and ironing machine anyone? 😆
.
.
I hope you enjoyed reading these fun facts! Come say hi in the comments and share a fun fact about yourself with me! ❤️

Sticky Note Rocket Counting 🚀
Check out this easy and fun Rocket Counting activity, using one of my all time favorite supplies, *drum rolls* sticky notes! Write the numbers, and draw circles as windows and astronauts on the sticky notes. Then invite your little one to match the number and the number of windows and astronauts with the number on the each rocket. Hope your little one will love this idea! 
.
.
Don’t forget to save this post and try this activity one day! Follow @happytotshelf for more easy and fun learning ideas for kids. If you love activities like this one, be sure to check out my activity membership, The Happy Learners’ Club (link in profile). ❤️
.
.

Super excited to showcase some of my favorite activities from our Space Theme Learning! First up, check out this Solar System Box I made from a tissue box! Children learn about the 8 planets and their positions from the Sun ☀️ . For the big kids, we also discussed about ordinal numbers (1st, 2nd, 3rd etc). 
.
.
Good news friends! By popular demand, doors to my activity membership, The Happy Learners’ Club will open next week from 1 to 5 August. This printable is included in our latest Space Theme Discovery Pack inside our membership. Now you can also create fun hands-on activities easily with these printables! Can’t wait to welcome new members into our THLC family!
.
.
.

We are zooming into a fun Space Theme Learning inside The Happy Learners’ Club next month! 🚀 My children tried and loved all the activities from the Space Theme Discovery Pack, and I can’t wait to share some of the fun activities with all of you. Just look at Abby, so happy and focused on making her Space Station Shape Puzzle. I’m just so thankful that I get to create these activities my children and for hundreds of families inside THLC. Swipe left to see how I set up the invitations to learn on our big table for all my 3 kids. Who’s ready for some fun space exploration and learning? 🚀 🌙 ☀️ 🌎 💫 
.
